BEGIN:VEVENT
X-SOURCE-URLS:{"Yolo Library": "https://events.yolocountylibrary.org/event/16176160"}
X-SOURCE-ID:yolo_library
SUMMARY:HERSTORY 3 -  Invisible No More: Chinese American Women Shaping Am
 erican Law
DTSTART;TZID=PST;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260307T110000
DTEND;TZID=PST;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260307T120000
UID:cad16fe571c916e9a4be4310beead164@events.yolocountylibrary.org
DESCRIPTION:In this powerful talk\, Dr. Chang C. Chen introduces Hersto
 ry 3\, the newest volume in her acclaimed Herstory series\, documenting 
 the legal history of Chinese American women from 2015–2024. The exhibit
  located at the Adult Nonfiction area.\n\n Contents: \n\n• How Chinese 
 American women helped shape U.S. case law—often against overwhelming odd
 s\n• Why their stories were nearly erased from history\n• The rise of
  Chinese American women judges and politicians in recent decades\n• Wh
 at Herstory reveals about justice\, visibility\, and belonging in America 
 today
LOCATION:*Children's Activity Room\, Mary L Stephens Davis Branch Library
URL:https://events.yolocountylibrary.org/event/16176160
X-SOURCE:Yolo Library
END:VEVENT
